HEADWORD: Stringhalt
<hw>String"halt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Far.)</fld>
<def>An habitual sudden twitching of the hinder leg of a horse, or an
involuntary or convulsive contraction of the muscles that raise the
hock.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>springhalt</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stringiness</ent>⟦br⟧
